criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age is greater than or equal to 18 years old and less than or equal to 80 years old;

          2. At least one imaging examination suggests the presence of carotid artery plaque;

          3. No allergy and other contraindications to ultrasound contrast;

          4. Contrast-enhanced ultrasound examination of carotid artery plaque is required;

          5. Volunteer to join this research project and sign informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who are unable to coordinate their body position or hold their breath during
             the ultrasound examination;

          2. Patients with severe lack of clinical data;

          3. During the follow-up, use drugs for the treatment of carotid plaque except
             lipid-lowering drugs, antiplatelet drugs, antioxidants, and calcium channel blockers;

          4. Follow up those who have lost contact;

          5. Ischemic stroke caused by non-carotid artery plaque shedding;

          6. Patients with atrial fibrillation and other serious heart diseases;

          7. A history of allergy to ultrasound contrast agents.
